message.content:
A 'Vireo philadelphicus' is a species of small North American songbird known commonly as the Philadelphia vireo. 
It has an olive-green crown and back, a white eyebrow, and yellow-green underparts. 
The wings and tail are dark brown, and the bill and legs are black. 
This bird can be found in deciduous forests during the breeding season and migrates to Central and South America during the winter. 
It feeds mainly on insects, but also consumes berries and fruit. 
The Philadelphia vireo is a rare bird to observe due to its shy behavior and preference for dense vegetation. 
It is primarily identified by its coloration and distinctive song.
